NIce report Brian.  Good to see you and Terry getting out...    I see some folks haven't changed...
That post made for an entertaining lunch hour ... Great report! Comical thread!

East wind was blowing when we arrived,the chop was about 1ft. Not knowing this lake very well,having only fished it twice for bass,I was thankful to have a great guide. Ali Bolly. Man this guy had marks all over the lake where he caught fish. To me this was MONEY.  Lots of tap tap taps on the harnesses,,but nothing to show.  We move to another spot. No tap tap taps. Ok,this is where the big fish live. After about 20 minutes of the harness,I switch up to a vibrax.Bolly puts on a body bait.  Start our troll. Oh my,I get a solid hit. Dinner????? Nope,in the slot limit,16.25. No pickeral bacon wraps.     Give the vibrax another go for a bit,nothing,so reworm the rig and out it goes. 30 ft behind the boat. Sitting there chatting away,and wham,no tic tic,just a wham bam. Fights on. Oh it,s a big pickeral. As it gets closer to the boat,I see a green streak go by. Oh my,it,s a musky. Ali says no,it,s a pike. I say (cant say what I said here. It,s a Musky. YAHOOOOOOOOOOO  After a short battle,it was landed.      You musky guys are doing it all wrong..   RIBBING,just in case you dont know me.  Ok truth be told,Ali and i were pickeral fishing,but this little guy(only my third ever,first two were with long time member Garry 2r,s) smacked my worm harness. It was a great battle. I could feel the braid ripping through the weeds,had to pull him out a few times.  Heading in,we hit our first spot that had lots of tap tap taps. Ali showed that you always go back to where you start.It was one that could of been taken,but we decided not,and left him to live another day.    All fish released to play with another angler another day. The cast Misfish,played by misfish  Ali Bolly,played by Terry.      Terry is nominated for outstanding Bolly giude service.  A fun day to report
well we're half way there......lol  I don't know where that east wind came from  most likely the east  it was a good day on the water
